args: Well, we made it! Oh, and this page is\nfrom a few years after that Dragonyule.
Urgh...my eyes... \nSo this is the Halidom years later.\nIt does seem to be in a festive mood.
Well, it WAS a special occasion...\nMuah ha ha ha!
＂Day 18, Month of the Raindragon\nToday, the palace was even noisier than usual.＂
＂Everyone's cheers of happiness grated on me,\nbut I couldn't blame them for their joy. After all...＂
Ah, it's a marriage celebration. Lovely!\nEr, but where is Cassandra?
Hard to believe someone actually\nagreed to marry you.
Still, congrats and all that. I hope you\nboth live long, happy lives.
*sigh* As for me, I never have been\ncomfortable with crowds and...so on.
I'm going to take a walk.\nI'll see you later.
Still, what is he supposed to say?\nWhat did I even WANT him to say?
＂I always knew it was going to come to this.\nI'm a sorceress and he's a king—and nothing\nwill ever change that.＂
＂I need to cast aside these feelings if I'm to\nremain by his side in even some capacity.＂
Oh, you nailed it, all right. Zing!\nTo her, Aurelius was no little brother.
Yet she chose to remain by his side and\nserve him for many years afterward, yes?
She is a strong woman indeed to set aside\nsuch feelings and do her duty.
Wait, you think she's strong? Pffffft!\nMuaaaaah ha ha ha ha!
Sorry! Sorry. It's just that you couldn't\nhave been more wrong if ya tried!
Here, lemme prove it to you. Muah ha!
We have arrived in the capital.
＂The palace maids can't stop gossiping about how\nthe young twins have taken their first steps.＂
＂I had to leave the palace to get away from\ntheir incessant chattering.＂
That's right. Over a decade ago, when\n{player_name} and his sister\nwere but infants.
This is your chance to see him when he\nwas an adowable widdle baby!
I'll thank you not to tease me, book!\nNow then, where is Cassandra?
There, in front of the gate.
Whyever is she dressed like that?

She was almost fifty at this point,
so she's tryin' to hide all the wrinkles
and crow's feet and gray hair you
people get when you get old.
Oh, you'll see why in a minute. Muah ha!
Thank you for carrying my things, dearie.\nI'll go the rest of the way by carriage.
Would you not at least wait for\nHis Majesty to return, ma'am?
It will be easier for me to leave\nwhile he isn't here.
If I may, ma'am, he seemed deeply\nsad that you are deciding to retire.
He's now a father of eight children but\nstill needs his big sister around, eh?
Still, I've made up my mind. Life as a\ncourt sorceress isn't bad, but there are\nSO many limitations on research.
I want to be able to research magic in\nwhatever way I choose, dearie—and to\ndo that, I need to be on my own.
Do you have any message you would\nlike me to relay to him, ma'am?
Just tell him to write me occasionally.
I said I was leaving to conduct whatever\nresearch I desired, but...
＂But that was a lie. I left because I needed\nto get away from Aurelius.＂
＂In the end, I simply couldn't silence those\nannoying feelings inside of me.＂
Zing! She couldn't get over the guy,\nyet chose to stay by his side anyway.\nEventually, she couldn't take it anymore.
What a whopper! What a zinger!\nWhat a terribly sad tale! Muaaah ha ha ha!
What a cruel, unkind thing you are!\nThe poor woman was simply—
What? Devoted? Loyal? Pffft!\nSpare me, sister. That lady was stuck in\nthe past and couldn't claw her way out.
You want proof? Take a look at THIS!
This is Cassandra's magical workshop.\nEr, but what is she drawing there?\nSome manner of magical sigil?
Yeah, this is four or five years ago,\nwhen she was about 60.
＂Day 13, Month of the Duskdragon.\nHis first letter in some time finally\nspurred me to action.＂
＂I knew full well he was busy with his duties in\nthe palace, and that he may have just written\nabout coming for a visit out of courtesy.＂
＂But just the thought he MIGHT come\nwas enough to spur me on to finish\nthe spell I'd been working on.＂
Right then! Once I activate it, everything\ninside the sigil will be created anew.\n...Er, theoretically, that is.

If it fails, someone's going to find this
old body festooned from the rafters like
so many party favors... But that's a risk
I'll take.

＂O ye who preside over the laws of
the abyss! Grant the blessing of new
birth to all who inhabit this sigil!＂
...And give me the body I want.
She's rebuilding her own body with\nthe power of MAAAAAAGIC!
Then the reason she appears so\nyoung in the current day...
I look just as I did before! But...
But I am still nothing but a fool.
Hey, she's not wrong—she IS a fool.
Because after going through all that\nsuffering to become young again,\nit ended up being all for nothing!
